# [IDR](../wg/idr.html)

## Summary

The Inter-Domain Routing (IDR) Working Group met at IETF 126 to discuss core BGP protocol updates, YANG models, routing enhancements, deployment guidelines, and security considerations. Key highlights included status updates on the core BGP specification revision (`draft-ietf-idr-bgp4-rfc4271bis`), finalizing `draft-ietf-idr-bgp-bfd-strict-mode` and the BGP FSM registry (`draft-ietf-idr-bgp-fsm-iana`) for Working Group Last Call, and transitioning the BGP YANG Model (`draft-ietf-idr-bgp-model`) towards publication. The group also evaluated several new individual proposals regarding routing in multi-plane scale-out networks, route reflector design, outbound route filtering (ORF) YANG models, next-hop selection enhancements, source-selective security mechanisms, canonical representation of path attributes, and threat modeling for BGP color extended communities.

