### 2. BGP BFD Strict-Mode & BGP FSM IANA Registrations
*   **Presenter:** Jeffrey Haas
*   **Slides:** [1-2. BGP BFD Strict-Mode](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-idr-sessa-1-2-bgp-bfd-strict-mode-00)
*   **Drafts:** `draft-ietf-idr-bgp-bfd-strict-mode`, `draft-ietf-idr-bgp-fsm-iana`
*   **Discussion:**
    *   Jeffrey Haas presented on the interoperability issues when initializing BGP and BFD, which can lead to deadlocks if one side starts BGP before BFD is up.
    *   The proposed solution leverages a BGP capability to hold the BGP state in the `OpenConfirm` substate until BFD comes up before sending a Keepalive.
    *   This required defining new Finite State Machine (FSM) events and substates, which are documented in the FSM IANA registration draft (`draft-ietf-idr-bgp-fsm-iana`) to assist with future management tools (e.g., YANG).
    *   Both documents have completed their technical updates, have at least three implementations, and are ready for WGLC.

