### 8. BGP Best Path Next-Hop Selection Enhancements
*   **Presenter:** Olivier Dugeon
*   **Slides:** [1-7. BGP best path next-hop selection enhancements](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-idr-sessa-1-7-bgp-best-path-next-hop-selection-enhancements-00)
*   **Discussion:**
    *   Olivier Dugeon argued that the RFC 4271 assumption that next-hops directly reflect forwarding is broken by modern underlays (SRv6, MPLS, SR Policies), leading to traffic drops or suboptimal routing.
    *   The draft proposes a "resolution preference" mechanism using a formalized path resolution tuple (forwarding address and optional context like color community) to allow operators to accurately align path selection with the forwarding intent.
    *   Chen Changli noted that this work overlaps with a draft he recently sent to the mailing list and requested coordination.
    *   Xiaohu Xu suggested that anycast next-hops with direct BGP sessions could solve this without protocol extensions. Jeffrey Haas requested this proposal be shared on the mailing list.
    *   John Scudder recommended thinking about how to make the next-hop resolvability condition pluggable in `draft-ietf-idr-bgp4-rfc4271bis` to simplify future specifications of this kind.

