### 11. BGP Enhancements for ECMP EBGP Scenarios
*   **Presenter:** Jeff Tantsura
*   **Slides:** [1-10.BGP Enhancements for ECMP EBGP Scenarios](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-idr-110-bgp-enhancements-for-ecmp-ebgp-scenarios-00)
*   **Discussion:**
    *   Jeff Tantsura presented on routing issues in parallel eBGP ECMP designs (e.g., modern data centers). Specifically, the persistent route selection defined in RFC 5004 is bypassed when paths arrive from parallel eBGP sessions.
    *   He proposed extending route persistent precedence across parallel eBGP peers and suppressing redundant route advertisements to parallel peers in the same AS.
    *   Jeffrey Haas noted that time-based changes to BGP path selection are historically prone to bugs and require exceptionally careful mailing list review.

